ionality.\nAnd very useful, bcs while zero speed line provides me a pic about the characteristic of the structural flows in some defined ranges, zero vanna literally marks tops and bottoms. I\u0027m gonna elaborate on this statement more in the future...\n*\n*\nFROM SUBSTACK CHAT CHRONOLOGY \n02-03 Feb 2025\n5955 is a crucial pivot for ES. I feel like it wants to retest 25 first. BTC also is heading towards 94k. lets see how it dances around 55 and will start to take long position on it. even tho i don\u0027t support futures trading that much\nthe main thought: you don\u0027t need to try to trade every wave. give it some time to show you what it wants to do. and only when you see it/feel it, and have a bias about the next move, trade it.\nso what i mean is that typicall mistake is when traders don\u0027t give it a time, but jump in a trade when they see the market moving in a direction.\nwhy? bcs it feels like you own the move, but in reality you are lagging already.\nwe don\u0027t trade moves that are happening, we trade underpriced opportunities. frontrunning the market\n*\nso: 5955 is a critical pivot area. you can also see it on my provided indicator, on a daily time frame. this area is - as i wrote in the post about the scripts - is for prove or disprove a move. this is a margin of error for mean retesting from any direction\nso if it shows strength below this lvl, you can be sure that 5922.71 ES is next. and in its environment is where i start to go long if i take any trades here.\ncan you see it? so I don\u0027t chase this gap down. but i have a bias that the market wants up into feb opex. but i also accept the fact that it moves both ways even tho if the avg trend is up or down. so i wait. and it does make sense, bcs if it goes down, traders will think it is the end. and thats when it will pay better, even on options\n*\nSome questions:\nspot down / gamma down. doesn\u0027t that mean when spot goes down market makers have to sell spot because they are short 