 understand how it works\n\n\n\n\n\n\nQ: Here\u0027s a question: considering only gamma, and excluding all the other variables...if the MM\u0027s are long 6050 and no other positions... they hedge ATM the delta 0.50. if price goes to 6060 the keep hedging a bit more, bc delta is higher, then 6070, same thing, a bit more hedge. yes? \nA: think about gamma as the amount dealers have to trade when spot moves by one unit. if you are long lets say 10 gamma, if spot moves up, you have to sell 10 shares of stocks to adjust your initial hedge (doesn\u0027t matter if you hedge call or put, the ending result is the same) okay, now we now that gamma changes relative to spot (called \"speed\"). so lets say one unit higher you only long 8 gamma means, if spot moves up, you will still sell against the price move, but only 8 shares of stocks this time. on the next lvl, you only long 5 gamma again, if spot moves up, you short sell only 5 shares of stocks. and so on... so price has less and less resistance from gamma based delta hedging, and it lets the range of returns expand slowly to the upside, causing RV to expand a bit. \nNow, if it reaches zero gamma line, then there is no gamma impact on that lvl when spot moves up or down, but then it flips to negative. And when you have negative gamma, lets say you short 5 gamma, if spot moves up, you have to BUY 5 more shares of stock. buying this time. \nquick math: if you are long ATM put: you have -50 delta, you long 50 shares of stock. in positive gamma exposure, lets say you long 2 gamma, if spot moves up by one unit, you will have -50 + 2 \u003d -48 delta to hedge, you only need to hedge 48 delta, so you sell 2 shares of stock now, in negative gamma exposure, if you would have short that 2 gamma, if spot moves up by one unit, you would have -50 + -2 \u003d -52, so you would have buy 2 more shares of stocks. if you are long ATM call: you long 50 delta, you short 50 shares of stock, long 2 gamma, spot up: 50 + 2 \u003d 52, sell 2 shares of stock short 2 gamma, spot up: 50 -2 \u003d 48, buy back 2 shares of stock. same thing happens with calls and puts\n"},{"ty":"ae","et":"inline","id":"i.7","epm":{"ee_eo":{"eo_bo":{"ln_s":0,"ln_w":0.0,"ln_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0}},"i_pid":null,"eo_mb":0.0,"i_ht":212.4,"eo_rtdf":{"rdf_ft":0},"eo_ml":0.0,"eo_mr":0.0,"eo_ad":null,"i_cid":"s-blob-v1-IMAGE-fUjPYi0_YPQ","i_cont":0.0,"eo_mt":0.0,"eo_type":0,"eo_lco":{"lc_oi":"","lc_cs":"","lc_ct":0,"lc_sci":"","lc_srk":""},"i_wth":481.9,"eo_at":null,"i_iwc":{"iwc_w":false},"eo_hb":false,"eo_rtd":"","i_crop":{"crop_oxr":-0.0,"crop_oyr":-0.0,"crop_rot":0.0,"crop_hr":1.0,"crop_wr":1.0},"i_iw":false,"i_rot":0.0,"i_clst":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":[]}},"i_bri":0.0,"i_msct":0,"i_src":null,"i_opa":1.0}}},{"ty":"ae","et":"positioned","id":"z.251660288.i.8","epm":{"pe_lo":-20.7,"pe_l":0,"ee_eo":{"eo_bo":{"ln_s":0,"ln_w":0.0,"ln_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0}},"i_pid":null,"eo_mb":0.0,"i_ht":247.2,"eo_rtdf":{"rdf_ft":0},"eo_ml":9.0,"eo_mr":9.0,"eo_ad":null,"i_cid":"s-blob-v1-IMAGE-so6gOjR-1PE","i_cont":0.0,"eo_mt":0.0,"eo_type":0,"eo_lco":{"lc_oi":"","lc_cs":"","lc_ct":0,"lc_sci":"","lc_srk":""},"i_wth":486.8,"eo_at":null,"i_iwc":{"iwc_w":false},"eo_hb":false,"eo_rtd":"","i_crop":{"crop_oxr":-0.0,"crop_oyr":-0.0,"crop_rot":0.0,"crop_hr":1.0,"crop_wr":1.0},"i_iw":false,"i_rot":0.0,"i_clst":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":[]}},"i_bri":0.0,"i_msct":0,"i_src":null,"i_opa":1.0},"pe_to":0.0}},{"ty":"te","id":"i.7","spi":41855},{"ty":"te","id":"z.251660288.i.8","spi":43288},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":41180,"ei":41180,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps_sm_i":true,"ps_ls_i":true,"ps_il_i":true,"ps_ir_i":true,"ps_al_i":true,"ps_bl_i":true,"ps_sd_i":true,"ps_sb_i":true,"ps_sa_i":true,"ps_lslm_i":true,"ps_br_i":true,"ps_bbtw_i":true,"ps_kwn_i":true,"ps_bt_i":true,"ps_ifl_i":true,"ps_bb_i":true,"ps_pbb_i":true}},{"ty":"as","st":"paragraph","si":41372,"ei":41372,"sm":{"ps_klt_i":true,"ps_awao_i":true,"ps