de, but it is not always this easy\nwhat i learned to check is to measure the ratio between my estimation vs their pricings and watch its trend (again ,the MOMENTUM) and when i see a constant diverge between them, i must know that something is going on it is a clear sign that they aggressively misprice the other side. this is the key!\nbcs normally it should fluctuate but when its not, then it is shady that some mispricing occurs purposely\nand this works the same way with markets, if you have read carefully my last three intraday post, you can recognize that logic. think about it\nso guys, this what i just explained here, is \nthe primal key to understand the markets, and frontrun it.\nsecond is the anomalies: momentum, mean reversion, mostly (read my post about efficient market, there i explained the most important ones) \nand the third is the positioning.\nso like in poker: \nfirst you check the odds, how they move, \nsecond, you check the reactions, the patterns,\nthird, you check the cards.\nand this is why i didn\u0027t start to post about greeks and all of these \u0027fancy stuffs\" yet, bcs it\u0027s not the most important thing.\nit is important if you are a market maker, otherwise it is secondary.\ni know a some good traders who don\u0027t even understand options market, and have 60%+ win rate. all they watch is momentum, mean reversion, and good risk management, and intuition for sentiment.\nI don\u0027t like when somebody wants to explain everything through positioning, bcs thats just not how it works. i showed a simple example above, with the risk reversal.\nAnd if you understand what i dropped in my educational posts, you will get the options market significance. it is huge, but different from how some interpreter it, overemphasizing it, like if this would be the only driver of the market... no. its customer sentiment. the supply/demand ratio for VOLATILITY\nI let you digest all of these :))\n\n\n*\nFrom market intraday post of 02/06/2025\nTO BE CLEAR: not the short fly, but the MM long fly is the short vol smile trade!\nIt is not directly suppresses volatily. not like the short fly pattern that is pinning and theta burning.\nMMs are longer gamma towards both wings, so in simulation, the momentum pingpongs between, the vol increases only when the momentum goes into the middle, but suppresses when it approaches the wings.\n"},{"ty":"ae","et":"inline","id":"i.10","epm":{"ee_eo":{"eo_bo":{"ln_s":0,"ln_w":0.0,"ln_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0}},"i_pid":null,"eo_mb":0.0,"i_ht":209.51293296887116,"eo_rtdf":{"rdf_ft":0},"eo_ml":0.0,"eo_mr":0.0,"eo_ad":null,"i_cid":"s-blob-v1-IMAGE--UD1SnG0xQs","i_cont":0.0,"eo_mt":0.0,"eo_type":0,"eo_lco":{"lc_oi":"","lc_cs":"","lc_ct":0,"lc_sci":"","lc_srk":""},"i_wth":412.6122047244094,"eo_at":null,"i_iwc":{"iwc_w":false},"eo_hb":false,"eo_rtd":"","i_crop":{"crop_oxr":-0.0,"crop_oyr":-0.0,"crop_rot":0.0,"crop_hr":1.0,"crop_wr":1.0},"i_iw":false,"i_rot":0.0,"i_clst":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":[]}},"i_bri":0.0,"i_msct":0,"i_src":null,"i_opa":1.0}}},{"ty":"ae","et":"inline","id":"i.9","epm":{"ee_eo":{"eo_bo":{"ln_s":0,"ln_w":0.0,"ln_c2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0}},"i_pid":null,"eo_mb":0.0,"i_ht":139.1,"eo_rtdf":{"rdf_ft":0},"eo_ml":0.0,"eo_mr":0.0,"eo_ad":null,"i_cid":"s-blob-v1-IMAGE-GCTxCC8bbPU","i_cont":0.0,"eo_mt":0.0,"eo_type":0,"eo_lco":{"lc_oi":"","lc_cs":"","lc_ct":0,"lc_sci":"","lc_srk":""},"i_wth":481.9,"eo_at":null,"i_iwc":{"iwc_w":false},"eo_hb":false,"eo_rtd":"","i_crop":{"crop_oxr":-0.0,"crop_oyr":-0.0,"crop_rot":0.0,"crop_hr":1.0,"crop_wr":1.0},"i_iw":false,"i_rot":0.0,"i_clst":{"cv":{"op":"set","opValue":[]}},"i_bri":0.0,"i_msct":0,"i_src":null,"i_opa":1.0}}},{"ty":"ae","et":"list","id":"kix.list.6","epm":{"le_nb":{"nl_4":{"b_gf":"%4","b_ts":{"ts_un":false,"ts_un_i":true,"ts_sc":false,"ts_it_i":true,"ts_fgc2":{"hclr_color":"#000000","clr_type":0},"ts_st_i":true,"ts_bgc2":{"hclr_color":null,"clr_type":0},"ts_fs_i":true,"ts_ff_i":false,"ts_bgc2_i":tru