s fly.\none of the wing will be magnetic. (based on the price, it is the upper one). and from there, it is vol burning.\nbut it also tells you intraday reversion potential to the zero vanna\nthe thing i empathized is the placing again, just like in the case of the PS on Monday. it basically prevents vol to expand too much to the downside by the dealer flow, while simultaneously keeps the upside long speed profile. and this telling me that the mass interest is up . this is the key conclusion\nQ: Hi Alma, on X post last year, you wrote\" For intraday trading I typically use 70-75 delta contracts.\". is that still valid? For 1-2dte 25delta?\nA: Now this is a good question.  The premium is different. ITMs are more expensive. OTMs are very cheap.\nFor intraday 0DTE trading I prefer ITMs mostly.\nWhy? Bcs the premium you pay for it includes intrinsic value that doesn\u0027t erode over time.\nATMs and OTMs only have extrinsic value that decay away by the time. Very important.\nI use ATM leg for 0DTE only if I know that I will hit it fast and close it fast, bcs ATM has the highest gamma.\nIf I want to take smaller position however, I prefer taking 1-2DTE, 25 delta contract.  Never 0DTE, bcs of fast time decay. It is cheap. \nFor longer-term trades like weekly monthly, I prefer 22-25 delta OTM strikes due to the gamma convexity,\nand when I see an opportunity, or a down stick to buy into it (but closer to the original leg\u0027s expo), I will add a 40-50 delta near-the-money or ATM leg too.\n07 Feb 2025\nMy Recap of the day: At the bell SPX rised to 2SD on hour time frame, At 10.00 data released dropped SPX to first reversion levels 68.2% and inside the 20p rolling range. Then at 10.51 after news by President Trump, VIX spiked up +6% at 16.25 and SPX dropped to 6033 (zero vanna level) as Alma suggested here:\nI expected this reversion yesterday. we got it today. depending on vol, I\u0027m gonna btd into opex 22 delta. I\u0027m off now  \n*\nThen Selling pressure remains eod🔴\n*\n☝️🟢It is mean reversion that happened today.\nI expected it for yesterday i dropped it on the chat, but it is only a mean reversion.\nWe went up all week, catched intraday bottoms. Vol remains crushed into next week, long bias remains as long as we hold the mean that you can read from the indicators on daily. This is why I provide lvls and charts.\nBelow the zero vanna and elevated vol you should have expected this and close the trade. Only bcs you potentially lost today, doesn\u0027t mean you are shit or this is shit. As wrote you at the beginning loss is the part of the game. Read my posts to learn about things, Take the time to properly digest them and discuss. It will be better. Self control and just go forward. Risk management is the part of the trading. Also dropped post about that.\nRegarding the dynamics around zero vanna vs vol happened Friday 07 feb at 6033 zero vanna lvl are:\nin very simplified terms for now: what is vanna? delta change to vol.\n·   \tpositive vanna \u003d positive correlation (vol up/delta up, vol down/delta down)\n·   \tnegative vanna \u003d negative relationship (vol up/delta down, vol down/delta up)\nif something goes from positive to negative and vice versa, it must have a zero too. thats the flip point.\nif we are in positive vanna regime, it also means positive speed, where MMs short downside gamma+vega, and long upside gamma+vega (bcs vanna is vega convexity too, vega change to spot, the delta of vega)\nNow, in this regime if spot moves down, MMs are shorter vol, so they buy vol, bidding up IV 20-22delta strikes. logical: vol up/delta up... if dealers are longer delta, they must sell futs, that increases vol. also bcs it is shorter donwisde gamma so less resistance from gamma \u003d more vol.\nBut, when spot reaches zero vanna line (that is not a stationary line but an oscillating territory), it all shifts. now vanna works reversely. so the higher the vol, the lower the delta will be pushed bcs spot went to negative vanna te